Excellent sequencing practice for clients with apraxia of speech. Targets broken into categories based on place of articulation and layered into gradually increasing levels of difficulty. Great companion to Kaufman Speech Praxis therapy.
It won't open.  I've emailed for troubleshooting and have yet to receive any reply. I'm trying to run this on a Samsung Galaxy tab E.
Ive been using this app to help my daughters speech at the advice of of speech therapist however ive been unable to download 2 syllables as i only have android devices please fix
I uninstalled for a time due to space concerns. Now I want it back and it won't - says "installed". Sheesh......
Running 4.4.2 android. Installed it twice and immediately it says it won't open. I was really excited to find an Apraxia  app and now it's just a big disappointment.

Subtitles under illustrations are partially hidden behind the progress indicator at the bottom of the screen. The level 7 and 8 buttons are also cut off, to the extent that they are almost unusable. This ia a wonderful app with partial words and illustrations of complete words. This app was just what we needed for home speech practice. It is best used when I can sit with my child and give my complete attention to pronunciation and correction. More illustrated words would be a great addition to this app. Thank you for the option of turning the voice over off.

Running android 4.3. We use restricted profiles for our kids.  Your app crashes when ran from a restricted profile.  Please fix ASAP. -- Just tried again today (fresh download and install) on android 4.4.4 and still has same issues as a secondary user (Aug 18 2014)
replyContent:
Hi Tim
We just submitted a 4.0 + compatible version.

content: I can't get the app to open.

This is built great for children with Apraxia.  My child was going to Speech class 2 times a week for her Apraxia.  I bought this program and have seen such amazing progress that we were able to cut the speech class down to 1 time a week.
I love the app.  Most of the wordsmare the same or similar to the ones we use at speech therapy.  I would like some words that begin with vowels though.  Overall a great app.
